By Chibuike Nwabuko  Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Senate President,  Dr.  Bukola Saraki has dared the former chairman of Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC),  Prof.  Attahiru Jega to be bold enough to name the Senate committee chairman he alleged to have collected bribe in the course of his duties.  Jega was said to have said during a lecture organised to mark the democracy day,  that committee  chairmen of the senate are known for collecting bribes.  Details Later. ..